verbose_text: Two classes of P-type Ca 2+ -ATPases participate in regulation of intracellular calcium levels; the P 2A -ATPases, also known as the sarcoplasmic-endoplasmic reticulum calcium ATPases (SERCA), and P 2B -ATPases known as plasma membrane calcium ATPases (PMCA), though PMCA pumps can also be found in intracellular organelles such as Golgi vesicles, vacuoles, and acidocalcisomes.
